data.title: Canadian Subhumans frontman Brian Goble dies, aged 57
data.meta_description: Canadian suffered a heart attack on December 7, according to reports
data.text:
Bassist, frontman and Canadian punk pioneer Brian Roy Goble – aka Wimpy Roy or Sunny Boy Roy – has died aged 57, according to reports.

The Vancouver Sun reports that Goble suffered a heart attack and passed away yesterday (December 7).

Goble took notable roles in three influential Vancouver punk bands, first as bassist in The Skulls, then as frontman of Subhumans (the Canadian group, not to be confused with the UK group of the same name) and finally as bass player in D.O.A.. Subhumans reunited in 2006.

Subhumans released their most recent album, a new version of their debut titled ‘Same Thoughts Different Day’, in 2010.
